{"id": 8039, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "3", "year": "2020", "session": "20N", "subtopic": "a-10-environmental-impact—heavy-metals", "title": "20N.3.HL.TZ0.5", "topic_id": "a", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Precipitation is one method used to treat waste water.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Phosphates, <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mi>PO</mi><mn>4</mn><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo></mrow></msubsup></math>, in waste water can be removed by precipitation with magnesium ions. </span><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>K</mi><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>p</mi></mrow></msub></math> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">of magnesium phosphate is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>24</mn></mrow></msup></math></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup><mo>(</mo><mi>aq</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><msub><mi>PO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup><mo>(</mo><mi>aq</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>→</mo><msub><mi>Mg</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>PO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><msub><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mo>)</mo></math><br/> </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> Calculate the maximum solubility of phosphate ions in a solution containing <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0100</mn><mo> </mo><mi>mol</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>dm</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math> magnesium ions.<br/> </span></p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[2]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px;\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Precipitation is one method used to treat waste water.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Zinc, cadmium, nickel, and lead are metal ions which can be removed by precipitation. Explain why waste water is adjusted to a pH of 9−10</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> to remove these ions by referring to section 32 of the data booklet.</span></p>\n<div class=\"marks\">[2]</div>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p><math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><msup><msub><mi>PO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><msub><mi>K</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">p</mi></mrow></msub><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><msup><mi>Mg</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mfenced><mn>3</mn></msup></mfrac></msqrt></math> ✔</p>\n<p><math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>«</mo><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><msup><msub><mi>PO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>−</mo></mrow></msup></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>«</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>24</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>0100</mn><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mo>»</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>02</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></msup><mo>«</mo><mi>mol</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>dm</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>»</mo></math> ✔</p>\n<p><br/><em>Accept “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>p</mi><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">=</mo><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">M</mi><msup><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">g</mi><mrow><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">3</mn></msup><msup><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">P</mi><msup><msub><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">O</mi><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">4</mn></msub><mrow><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">3</mn><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">-</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">2</mn></msup></math>” for M1.</em><br/><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p><em>Any two of:</em><br/>precipitation occurs with a base/carbonate/<math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>−</mo></mrow></msup></math>/hydroxide/<math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>OH</mi><mo>−</mo></msup></math> ✔</p>\n<p><math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\"><msup><mi>OH</mi><mo>−</mo></msup></mfenced></math> is high enough to cause metal hydroxide precipitation at that <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>pH</mi></math> ✔</p>\n<p>these ions are slightly acidic/more soluble in acidic conditions ✔</p>\n<p>only small amounts of carbonate/hydroxides/anion needed at that <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>pH</mi></math> ✔</p>\n<p>solubility products of the hydroxides are very small ✔</p>\n<p><em>Do <strong>not</strong> accept “hydroxyl” for “hydroxide”.</em></p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>The Ksp problem was very well answered by the stronger candidates, who had no difficulty working out the maximum solubility of phosphate ions in solution as 1.02 x 10<sup>-9</sup> mol dm<sup>-3</sup>.</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">a.</div>\n</div><div class=\"question\" style=\"padding-left: 20px;\">\n<p>This question although somewhat challenging was well answered by the stronger candidates.</p>\n<div class=\"question_part_label\">b.</div>\n</div>"}